      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Xylose is a common sugar found in many types of wood, including maple and cherry. Because it is much less prone to cause tooth decay than sucrose, xylose has been used in candy and chewing gum. Assign <i>R</i> or <i>S</i> configurations to the chirality centers in xylose.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBb0VSIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--e5936f1a5f44f57c00496003ce67c6bfb179ccab/OChem_05_EC_016.jpg\" alt=\"Acyclic wedge-dash structure of (plus)-xylose.\">",
